{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012HErUFgsRFpEBoFeuDzFKP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RzSo9uYC5gmmjMEJSeatp4","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade Change Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16  \n**Cluster:** `crdb-cluster` in namespace `cockroachdb`  \n**Change type:** Minor-version upgrade (v24.1.0 → v24.2.x)  \n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — do not apply during the review window\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot\n\n### 1.1 Version and Nodes\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| CockroachDB image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| Build date | 2024-05-15 |\n| Cluster version setting | `24.1` |\n| StatefulSet replicas | 3 |\n| Pod management policy | `Parallel` |\n\n**Node liveness at time of audit (2026-06-17T00:50 UTC):**\n\n| Node | Address | is_available | is_live |\n|------|---------|--------------|---------|\n| 1 (crdb-cluster-0) | crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257 | true | true |\n| 2 (crdb-cluster-1) | crdb-cluster-1.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257 | true | true |\n| 3 (crdb-cluster-2) | crdb-cluster-2.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257 | **false** | **false** |\n\n> **Pre-upgrade gate:** Node 3 is currently unavailable. The upgrade MUST NOT begin until all three nodes are live and available. Investigate crdb-cluster-2 before scheduling the maintenance window.\n\n### 1.2 StatefulSet Configuration\n\n| Parameter | Current value |\n|-----------|--------------|\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| CPU request/limit | `1` core |\n| Memory request/limit | `2Gi` |\n| PVC size | `10Gi` (ReadWriteOnce) |\n| `--cache` | `25%` of pod memory → ~512 MiB |\n| `--max-sql-memory` | `25%` of pod memory → ~512 MiB |\n| TLS mode | TLS enabled; certs from Secret `cockroachdb-node-certs` |\n| Cert secret keys | `ca.crt`, `node.crt`, `node.key`, `client.root.crt`, `client.root.key` |\n| Update strategy | `RollingUpdate` (partition: 0) |\n| Termination grace period | `60 s` |\n\n### 1.3 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\nThese were live at audit time (`value != default_value`):\n\n| Setting | Current value | Note |\n|---------|--------------|------|\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | `true` | Explicitly enabled; verify default after upgrade |\n| `kv.range_merge.queue.enabled` | `false` | Auto-merge disabled; intentional tuning — must be preserved |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | `208 MiB` | Raised above default; intentional tuning — must be preserved |\n| `version` | `24.1` | Cluster protocol version; bumped as final upgrade step |\n| `cluster.secret` | `6fe82743-…` | Telemetry anonymization token; not upgrade-sensitive |\n\n### 1.4 Zone Configurations\n\nAll zones at audit time:\n\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | range_min_bytes | range_max_bytes |\n|--------|-------------|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|\n| `RANGE default` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `DATABASE system` | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE meta` | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE system` | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE liveness` | 5 | 600 (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `TABLE system.public.lease` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_stats` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_statistics` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.tenant_usage` | (inherited) | 7200 (2 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_activity` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_activity` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n\nNotable tuning decisions:\n- System ranges (`meta`, `system`, `liveness`, `DATABASE system`) carry **5 replicas** against the 3-node cluster. This is valid (replicas > nodes is allowed and improves resilience for critical metadata), but means up-replication can never fully satisfy the constraint until more nodes are added.\n- `RANGE default` and user tables use **3 replicas** (matches node count).\n- `gc.ttlseconds = 14400` on `RANGE default` is a custom value (CockroachDB ships `90000` by default).\n\n### 1.5 User Data\n\n| Schema | Tables |\n|--------|--------|\n| `defaultdb.tenant_a` | `table_a`, `table_b` |\n| `defaultdb.tenant_b` | `table_c`, `table_d` |\n\n`tenant_b.table_c` and `tenant_b.table_d` have explicit zone configs (see §1.4).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target State\n\n| Item | From | To |\n|------|------|----|\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x` (latest v24.2 patch) |\n| `version` cluster setting | `24.1` | `24.2` (finalized after all nodes upgraded) |\n| All other cluster settings | unchanged | unchanged |\n| All zone configs | unchanged | unchanged |\n| StatefulSet replicas | 3 | 3 (unchanged) |\n| TLS / certs | unchanged | unchanged |\n\n> CockroachDB requires upgrading one minor version at a time. v24.1 → v24.2 is a single-step upgrade. Skipping to v25.x is not supported.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\nVerify all items before the maintenance window begins:\n\n- [ ] **All 3 nodes live and available** — `kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`; confirm `is_live=true` and `is_available=true` for nodes 1–3. Resolve crdb-cluster-2 unavailability first.\n- [ ] **No active schema changes** — `SELECT * FROM crdb_internal.schema_changes;` returns zero rows.\n- [ ] **No under-replicated ranges** — `SELECT range_id FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases WHERE lease_holder = 0;` returns zero rows; Admin UI replication dashboard shows 0 under-replicated.\n- [ ] **Backup completed** — a full cluster backup is stored off-cluster and verified restorable.\n- [ ] **Target image available** — confirm `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x` is pullable from the node image registry (or pre-pulled on each node).\n- [ ] **Review v24.2 release notes** for any deprecated settings or changed defaults that intersect with the non-default settings in §1.3.\n- [ ] **PodDisruptionBudget** — confirm a PDB exists or is applied that tolerates exactly 1 unavailable replica during the rolling restart.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 1 — Update the StatefulSet image (rolling restart, one pod at a time)\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x\n```\n\nThe `RollingUpdate` strategy (partition: 0) restarts pods one at a time in\nreverse ordinal order (crdb-cluster-2, crdb-cluster-1, crdb-cluster-0). The\ncluster remains available throughout (RF-3 tolerates one node down).\n\n**Wait between pods:** after each pod restarts, verify it rejoins before the\nnext one is replaced:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs\n```\n\nConfirm `is_live=true` for the restarted node before proceeding.\n\n### Step 2 — Finalize the cluster version\n\nOnce all three nodes report `v24.2.x` in `node status`:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = '24.2';\"\n```\n\nThis is a one-way operation. Do not run it until every node is on v24.2.\n\n### Step 3 — Re-assert custom cluster settings\n\nVerify the non-default settings survived the upgrade (new minor versions\noccasionally reset settings whose defaults change):\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings\n      WHERE variable IN (\n        'kv.range_merge.queue.enabled',\n        'kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate',\n        'diagnostics.reporting.enabled'\n      );\"\n```\n\nIf any value has reverted to its new default, re-apply the intended value:\n\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.range_merge.queue.enabled = false;\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '208 MiB';\nSET CLUSTER SETTING diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true;\n```\n\n### Step 4 — Verify zone configs are intact\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n```\n\nConfirm all entries from §1.4 are present and unchanged. Re-apply any that\ndiverged using the exact SQL from §1.4.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\nCockroachDB does not support downgrading after `SET CLUSTER SETTING version`\nis finalized. The rollback window closes at the end of Step 2.\n\n**Before Step 2 (image only, version not yet bumped):**\n\nRevert the StatefulSet image and allow the rolling restart to proceed in\nreverse:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n```\n\nNodes still running v24.1 can interoperate with nodes that were temporarily\non v24.2 without the version bump, so the cluster stays coherent during\nrollback.\n\n**After Step 2 (version finalized):** rollback is not possible. Restore from\nthe pre-upgrade backup.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Post-Upgrade Validation\n\n- [ ] All 3 nodes live and available on v24.2.x — `node status`\n- [ ] `SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;` returns `24.2`\n- [ ] Non-default cluster settings match §1.3 (verified in Step 3)\n- [ ] Zone configs match §1.4 (verified in Step 4)\n- [ ] No under-replicated ranges (Admin UI or SQL)\n- [ ] Application read/write smoke test against `defaultdb.tenant_a` and `defaultdb.tenant_b`\n- [ ] Run `SHOW JOBS;` — confirm no stuck migration jobs\n- [ ] Capture a post-upgrade snapshot of cluster settings for audit trail\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|--------|------------|\n| crdb-cluster-2 is already unhealthy | Confirmed | High — upgrade with 1 node down leaves no fault tolerance | **Block upgrade until resolved** |\n| Setting default changes in v24.2 reset custom values | Low | Medium — merge queue re-enabled could cause unexpected range activity | Re-assert in Step 3 immediately after version bump |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 208 MiB` causes network saturation during rebalance after upgrade | Low | Low | Monitor network throughput; reduce if needed post-upgrade |\n| System ranges (5 replicas on 3 nodes) cannot fully satisfy replication constraint | Existing | Low | Not introduced by upgrade; document as known state; address by adding nodes if required |\n| PVC capacity (10 GiB) insufficient post-upgrade due to new internal tables | Very low | Medium | Check disk usage before upgrade; expand PVCs if usage > 70% |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Contacts and Approvals\n\n| Role | Name / Team | Sign-off required |\n|------|-------------|------------------|\n| DBA / cluster owner | — | Yes |\n| On-call engineer | — | Yes (must be available during window) |\n| Change advisory | — | Yes (CAB approval before maintenance window) |\n\n**Planned maintenance window:** TBD — schedule after crdb-cluster-2 is healthy.\n\n---\n\n*This document was generated from a live cluster audit on 2026-06-16. Re-audit if more than 7 days elapse before the maintenance window.*\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":484,"cache_read_input_token