, `client.root.crt`, `client.root.key` |\n| Update strategy | `RollingUpdate` (partition: 0) |\n| Termination grace period | `60 s` |\n\n### 1.3 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\nThese differ from their compiled-in defaults at audit time:\n\n| Setting | Current value | Note |\n|---------|--------------|------|\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | `true` | Explicitly enabled; verify default in v24.2 |\n| `kv.range_merge.queue.enabled` | `false` | Auto-merge disabled — intentional tuning, must be preserved |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | `208 MiB` | Raised above default — intentional tuning, must be preserved |\n| `version` | `24.1` | Cluster protocol version; bumped as final upgrade step |\n| `cluster.secret` | `6fe82743-...` | Telemetry anonymization token; not upgrade-sensitive |\n\n### 1.4 Zone Configurations\n\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | range_min_bytes | range_max_bytes |\n|--------|-------------|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|\n| `RANGE default` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `DATABASE system` | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE meta` | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE system` | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE liveness` | 5 | 600 (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `TABLE system.public.lease` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_stats` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_statistics` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.tenant_usage` | (inherited) | 7200 (2 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_activity` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_activity` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| `TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n\nNotable tuning:\n- System ranges (`meta`, `system`, `liveness`, `DATABASE system`) carry **5 replicas** on a 3-node cluster. This is intentional for critical metadata durability but means the constraint is nominally over-subscribed until nodes are added.\n- `RANGE default` gc.ttlseconds=14400 is a custom value (the CRDB default is 90000).\n\n### 1.5 User Data\n\n| Schema | Tables |\n|--------|--------|\n| `defaultdb.tenant_a` | `table_a`, `table_b` |\n| `defaultdb.tenant_b` | `table_c`, `table_d` |\n\n`tenant_b.table_c` and `tenant_b.table_d` carry explicit zone configs (see §1.4).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target State\n\n| Item | From | To |\n|------|------|----|\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x` (latest v24.2 patch at upgrade time) |\n| `version` cluster setting | `24.1` | `24.2` (set after all nodes upgraded) |\n| All cluster settings | see §1.3 | unchanged |\n| All zone configs | see §1.4 | unchanged |\n| StatefulSet replicas | 3 | 3 (unchanged) |\n| TLS / certs | Secret `cockroachdb-node-certs` | unchanged |\n| Resources (CPU/mem/PVC) | see §1.2 | unchanged |\n\n> CockroachDB requires upgrading one minor version at a time. v24.1 → v24.2 is a supported single-step upgrade. Do not skip to v25.x.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\nAll items must be confirmed before the maintenance window begins:\n\n- [ ] **All 3 nodes live and available** — run `node status`; confirm `is_live=true` and `is_available=true` for nodes 1–3. **crdb-cluster-2 is currently unhealthy — must be resolved first.**\n- [ ] **No active schema changes** — `SELECT * FROM crdb_internal.schema_changes;` returns zero rows.\n- [ ] **No under-replicated ranges** — Admin UI replication dashboard shows 0 under-replicated ranges.\n- [ ] **Full backup completed and verified** — store off-cluster; confirm restore is possible before beginning.\n- [ ] **Target image pullable** — confirm `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x` is accessible from the cluster's image registry (or pre-pulled).\n- [ ] **v24.2 release notes reviewed** — check for deprecated settings or changed defaults that intersect §1.3.\n- [ ] **PodDisruptionBudget in place** — confirm a PDB exists that tolerates exactly 1 unavailable pod.\n- [ ] **Disk usage acceptable** — PVC usage below 70% on each node to accommodate any new internal tables.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 1 — Rolling image update\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x\n```\n\nThe `RollingUpdate` strategy (partition: 0) restarts pods one at a time in\nreverse ordinal order: crdb-cluster-2, then crdb-cluster-1, then crdb-cluster-0.\nThe cluster remains available throughout because RF-3 tolerates one node down.\n\n**Gate between each pod:** after each restart, verify the node rejoins before\nthe next one is replaced:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs\n```\n\nProceed only when the restarted node shows `is_live=true`.\n\n### Step 2 — Finalize the cluster version\n\nOnce all three nodes report `v24.2.x` in `node status`:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = '24.2';\"\n```\n\n**This is a one-way, irreversible operation.** Do not execute until every node\nis confirmed on v24.2. After this point the rollback path via image revert is\nclosed.\n\n### Step 3 — Verify and re-assert custom cluster settings\n\nCheck that non-default settings survived the upgrade:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs -e \"\nSELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings\nWHERE variable IN (\n  'kv.range_merge.queue.enabled',\n  'kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate',\n  'diagnostics.reporting.enabled'\n);\"\n```\n\nIf any value has reverted, re-apply:\n\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.range_merge.queue.enabled = false;\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '208 MiB';\nSET CLUSTER SETTING diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true;\n```\n\n### Step 4 — Verify zone configs are intact\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n```\n\nConfirm all entries from §1.4 are present and unchanged. If any zone config was\nreset by the upgrade, re-apply the exact SQL from §1.4.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\nThe rollback window exists only **before Step 2** (before `version` is set to `24.2`).\n\n**Before Step 2 — revert the image:**\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n```\n\nNodes that briefly ran v24.2 without the version bump can interoperate with\nv24.1 nodes, so the cluster stays coherent during the image rollback.\n\n**After Step 2 — image rollback is not possible.** The cluster version is\npermanent. Restore from the pre-upgrade backup taken in the pre-upgrade checklist.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Post-Upgrade Validation\n\n- [ ] All 3 nodes live and available on v24.2.x (`node status`)\n- [ ] `SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;` returns `24.2`\n- [ ] Custom cluster settings match §1.3 values (verified in Step 3)\n- [ ] Zone configs match §1.4 (verified in Step 4)\n- [ ] Admin UI shows 0 under-replicated ranges\n- [ ] Application smoke test: read and write against `defaultdb.tenant_a` and `defaultdb.tenant_b`\n- [ ] `SHOW JOBS;` — no stuck migration jobs\n- [ ] Post-upgrade audit snapshot: capture `SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings WHERE value != default_value;` and `SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;` for the audit record\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|--------|------------|\n| crdb-cluster-2 already unhealthy at upgrade start | Confirmed existing | **High** — upgrading with one node down leaves zero fault tolerance | **Hard block:** resolve before scheduling window |\n| v24.2 changes a default that silently resets a custom setting | Low | Medium — e.g., re-enabling merge queue causes unexpected range activity | Re-assert all settings in Step 3 immediately after version bump |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 208 MiB` saturates network during post-upgrade rebalance | Low | Low | Monitor network throughput during Step 1; reduce rate temporarily if needed |\n| System ranges (5 replicas on 3 nodes) remain over-subscribed after upgrade | Pre-existing | Low | Not introduced by this upgrade; document as known state; address by adding nodes separately |\n| PVC headroom insufficient for new internal v24.2 tables | Very low | Medium | Check disk usage in pre-upgrade checklist; expand PVCs if >70% full |\n| Rolling restart triggers readiness probe failures | Low | Low | Existing probes (initialDelaySeconds=10, failureThreshold=2) are tuned conservatively; monitor pod events during Step 1 |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Contacts and Approvals\n\n| Role | Action required |\n|------|----------------|\n| DBA / cluster owner | Review and sign off on §1–§4 |\n| On-call engineer | Must be available for the full duration of the maintenance window |\n| Change advisory board | CAB approval required before maintenance window is scheduled |\n\n**Planned maintenance window:** TBD — **do not schedule until crdb-cluster-2 is healthy and all pre-upgrade checklist items are green.**\n\n---\n\n*This plan was generated from a live cluster audit on 2026-06-16. Re-audit if more than 7 days elapse before the maintenance window to catch any configuration drift.*\nPLANEOF\necho \"Exit: $?\"","description":"Write migration plan to /tmp/plan.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5180,"cache_read_input_tokens":34807,"output_tokens":3880,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5180,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":3880,"cache_read_input_tokens":34807,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5180},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":{"applied_edits":[]}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c49f3d6-57eb-4b4e-95e8-0bd185f5f154","uuid":"956983ec-0aab-4008-990f-8c640cd4c28a","request_id":"req_011Cc7v6sSemwKBjVKMZWtCa"}
